Package exceptions

package exceptions
Exceptions package is a package that contains all exceptions that are needed to operate this app.
  • Exceptions
    Class
    Description
    EmptyArgumentException
    Is thrown when the argument is empty.
    IncorrectInputInScriptException
    Is thrown when input in script is incorrect.
    MustNotBeEmptyException
    Is thrown when input is empty.
    NotInDeclaredLimitsException
    Is thrown when passed value is not in declared limits.
    NotUniqueIdException
    Is thrown if Id is not unique
    ScriptRecursionException
    Is thrown when script is recursive
    WrongAmountOfArgumentsException
    Is thrown when the amount of arguments is wrong.
